leadership-approach|process_vision_people_results|graduated|process|vision|people|results|Process through to Results|This pattern can make leadership feel coherent because the order gives a clear sequence: Process first, then Vision, then People, with Results added deliberately when needed.|It can become too narrow when the early signals settle the work before Results has been considered. The later signal is range that may change what the pattern notices.|Remember the sequence, but do not let it become a fixed rule; firmer decision, ownership, and follow-through may be the missing piece in some situations.|The overall pattern is a stepped leadership approach. It tends to move from clarity, sequencing, standards, and dependable structure towards trust, communication, inclusion, development, and relational judgement, while Results gives the pattern a further check when the situation needs a fuller response.|active|leadership-approach::process_vision_people_results::graduated
leadership-approach|process_vision_people_results|balanced|process|vision|people|results|A flexible Process, Vision, People, and Results pattern|This pattern can make leadership feel adaptable because several routes are available: Process, Vision, People, and Results. The value lies in matching the response to the situation rather than proving one route is always right.|It can become too narrow when the leader moves between routes without making the current priority clear. Others may then struggle to tell whether the work now needs clarity, sequencing, standards, and dependable structure, direction, framing, possibility, meaning, and future consequence, trust, communication, inclusion, development, and relational judgement, or outcomes, decisions, ownership, and follow-through.|Remember that flexibility still needs clarity; name the leadership need that matters most in the moment.|The overall pattern is a balanced leadership approach with several usable ways into the work. Context matters: different moments may call for progress, structure, direction, or trust, and the pattern works best when that choice is made visible.|active|leadership-approach::process_vision_people_results::balanced
leadership-approach|process_people_results_vision|concentrated|process|people|results|vision|Process at the centre|This pattern can make leadership feel clear because Process gives the response a strong centre: making work easier to coordinate, repeat, and hand over without avoidable confusion. People and Results add range without removing that first point of focus.|It can become too narrow when the method keeps being refined after the situation needs movement, meaning, or direct conversation. Vision is the deliberate range that keeps the pattern rounded when the first response has done its job.|Remember that good intent needs a dependable way of working, but it still needs stronger direction, meaning, and future context when the situation asks for more range.|The overall pattern is a leadership approach that starts by trusting clarity, sequencing, standards, and dependable structure. At its best, it gives people a clear way into the work while still leaving room for People, Results, and Vision to complete the picture.|active|leadership-approach::process_people_results_vision::concentrated
