leadership-approach|vision_results_process_people|concentrated|vision|results|process|people|Vision at the centre|This pattern can make leadership feel clear because Vision gives the response a strong centre: helping people understand why the work matters and what it is meant to lead towards. Results and Process add range without removing that first point of focus.|It can become too narrow when the future frame stays open after the work needs a decision, structure, or people grounding. People is the deliberate range that keeps the pattern rounded when the first response has done its job.|Remember that the current choice needs a reason beyond the immediate task, but it still needs clearer communication, inclusion, and shared commitment when the situation asks for more range.|The overall pattern is a leadership approach that starts by trusting direction, framing, possibility, meaning, and future consequence. At its best, it gives people a clear way into the work while still leaving room for Results, Process, and People to complete the picture.|active|leadership-approach::vision_results_process_people::concentrated
